cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing tasks such as keyphrase generation. It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a recurrent generative model for keyphrase generation. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as keyphrase generation is a sub-task of information retrieval. The paper also proposes new metrics for evaluation, which could place it under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
